title: Blair's institute continued to receive Saudi money after journalist's murder
description: Sir Tony Blair's institute has continued to advise and receive money from Saudi Arabia's government since the murder of the journalist Jamal Khashoggi, it has emerged.

title: Investigation launched into claims record-breaking mountaineers climbed over dying porter on K2
description: An investigation has been launched into claims climbers left a porter to die near the peak of the world's most treacherous mountain, a mountaineer has said.

title: England through to semi-final after beating Colombia in Women's World Cup
description: The Lionesses have secured a spot in the semi-finals of the Women's World Cup after beating Colombia 2-1.

description: It was the first time the people of Lahaina had been allowed to return since wildfires laid ruin to their town three days ago.

title: At least one person dead and dozens rescued after migrant boat crossing Channel capsizes
description: At least one person has died and dozens of others have been rescued after a migrant boat crossing the English Channel capsized.

title: Harry Kane pictured in Bayern Munich shirt as he signs for German champions
description: Harry Kane has signed his contract with Bayern Munich and completed a medical ahead of his £100m move from Tottenham.

title: The 1975 sued for £2m after Matty Healy kissed male bandmate on stage at Malaysia festival
description: The 1975 are being pursued for more than £2m in damages after frontman Matty Healy criticised Malaysia's homosexuality laws and kissed a male bandmate on stage.
